head
  link(rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css")
  link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto|Roboto+Mono|Questrial")
  link(rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css")
  script(src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-latest.min.js" type="text/javascript")
  title Free Code Camp API Project
body
  h1 File Metadata Microservice
  div.container
    h2 Try it out
    br
    br
    small Limit 1 MB
    br
    button.upload-button#upload-button
      label(for="file-input") Upload file
    input.file-input#file-input(type="file")
    button.submit-button#submit-button Submit
    div.file-display#file-name
    div.error#error
  script(type="text/javascript" src="/client.js")
  br
  br
  div.content
    p This is a REST API microservice which will tell you the size of your file (bytes).
    h2 Submitting a file:
    h4 Example request:
    div.code POST https://dcthetall-file-metadata.herokuapp.com/api/file/size
    p with the following request body
    div.code { "fileUrl": [file_as_base64_URL_string] }
    h4 Example response:
    div.code { "filename": "data/[epoch_time].[file_extension]" }
    h2 Getting the file's size:
    h4 Example request:
    p Using the file name from the POST request response
    div.code GET https://dcthetall-file-metadata.herokuapp.com/api/file/size?name=[file_name]
    h4 Example response:
    div.code { "size": [file_size_in_bytes] }
    p Note that you can only request the size once per file.
